of the solution properties together with membrane and F-actin binding interfaces suggest that GAC adopts several conformations from closed to open and extended. A multi-conformational model for assembly and regulation of GAC within the glideosome is proposed.</p></abstract><kwd-group kwd-group-type="research-organism"><title>Research organism</title><kwd>Human</kwd><kwd><italic>P. falciparum</italic></kwd><kwd>Other</kwd></kwd-group><funding-group><award-group id="par-1"><funding-source><institution-wrap><institution-id institution-id-type="FundRef">http://dx.doi.org/10.13039/501100000275</institution-id><institution>Leverhulme Trust</institution></institution-wrap></funding-source><award-id>RPG_2018_107</award-id><principal-award-recipient><name><surname>Matthews</surname><given-names>Stephen</given-names></name></principal-award-recipient></award-group><award-group id="par-2"><funding-source><institution-wrap><institution-id institution-id-type="FundRef">http://dx.doi.org/10.13039/501100000268</institution-id><institution>Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council</institution></institution-wrap></funding-source><award-id>BB/W001764/1</award-id><principal-award-recipient><name><surname>Matthews</surname><given-names>Stephen</given-names></name></principal-award-recipient></award-group><award-group id="par-3"><funding-source><institution-wrap><institution-id institution-id-type="FundRef">http://dx.doi.org/10.13039/100013325</institution-id><institution>Swiss Re Foundation</institution></institution-wrap></funding-source><award-id>10030_185325</award-id><principal-award-recipient><name><surname>Soldati-Favre</surname><given-names>Dominique</given-names></name></principal-award-recipient></award-group><award-group id="par-4"><funding-source><institution-wrap><institution-id institution-id-type="FundRef">http://dx.doi.org/10.13039/100013325</institution-id><institution>Swiss Re Foundation</institution></institution-wrap></funding-source><award-id>CRSII5_19